The Ogun State governor, Prince Dapo Abiodun, has felicitated with the former governor of Lagos State, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu on his 69th birthday. In a statement signed by his spokesman, Kunle Somorin, Abiodun described the National Leader of the All Progressives Congress, APC as a political icon who has worked for the growth and development of the country. According to Abiodun, the elder statesman was able to stand out among his equals due to his strides in business and governance. The governor said Tinubu ensured that the Southwest benefited from the APC-led Federal Government. “On behalf of my family, the Government and the good people of Ogun State, I felicitate the National Leader of our great party, All Progressives Congress (APC) and statesman, H.E. Senator Bola Ahmed Tinubu on his 69th birthday. “Your towering accomplishments, from the corporate world to being Senator of the Federal Republic, representing Lagos West to being elected twice as Governor and as the only governor standing during the 2003 Tsunami are testimonies of a political icon. The governor prayed that God grants the APC leader more grace and longer life to continue his good works.